snippet: The system opened Saturday and performed much better than last year, but some consumers reported long delays in trying to buy insurance and access their accounts at HealthCare.gov.
abstract: Federal health insurance marketplace opens for business and performs much better than in 2013, but some consumers report long, frustrating delays in trying to buy insurance and gain access to their accounts at HealthCare.gov.

byline.original: By ROBERT PEAR and ABBY GOODNOUGH
byline.contributor: Mauricio Guerrero contributed reporting from Houston, Matt Hamilton from Los Angeles and Colin Moynihan from New York.

lead_paragraph: The system opened Saturday and performed much better than last year, but some consumers reported long delays in trying to buy insurance and access their accounts at HealthCare.gov.

headline.main: Some New Frustrations as Health Exchange Opens
